Source:  High Country
Author:  McLEOD
Vol / Page:  5
Edition:
Quote:  So the musterer of to-day, with his pack of five or six dogs, began to take shape. One or two of the border type - `heading dogs' as they're called now and three or four huntaways and `handy' dogs. <i>ibid.</i> 46 . . .Wait, the most wonderful dog i ever saw, a true `handy' dog. He would bring sheep out of any place where dog or sheep could go, and all his master ever said to him was `Here Wait! Here Wait!'; the rest was left to his own judgment and initiative and the sheep would be got.
